<div id="banner">
	<h1>iCal!</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>So today Apple released <a href="http://www.apple.com/ical/">iCal</a>, the Internet calendaring component of their application suite. It imports straight from Entourage, lets you publish calendars to the Web (<a href="http://ical.mac.com/aaronsw/Travel">here&#8217;s my travel calendar</a>) and <a href="webcal://ical.mac.com/aaronsw/Travel.ics">subscribe to it with one click</a> (although they invented a new URI scheme&#8230;).</p>

<p>It integrates with Address Book (drag user to news item to invite them) and Mail (uses it to send invitations). Here at the OpenForce office, I&#8217;m converting all the Entourage users over.</p>

<p class="posted">posted September 10, 2002 10:49 AM (<a class="category" href="cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000579" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

